Madagascar Plans to Reduce Income Tax Rates in 2012, Midi Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-10-18T13:36:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/madagascar-plans-to-reduce-income-tax-rates-in-2012-midi-says.html
Madagascar plans to cut income tax
rates next year, Midi Madagasikara reported, citing Finance
Minister Hery Rajaonarimampianina.  The  budget deficit  for the 2012 fiscal year will probably
be less than 3 percent of gross domestic product, the
Antananarivo-based newspaper cited the minister as saying on its
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
